				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">speaking as a wizard, a pet casting ice comet is actually fine with me, and honestly a poor spell choice if they are also casting draughts.
<br />

<br />
the cast time and mana use of ice comet makes it horridly ineffciant vs the draught spells.
<br />

<br />
my idea of a perfect child of ro pet?
<br />

<br />
Draught of fire
<br />
Draught of ice
<br />
Voltaic draught 
<br />
Manaskin
<br />
Markar's discord
<br />
Manasink
<br />
lure of frost
<br />
lure of flame
<br />
lure of lightning
<br />

<br />
Snare for mages, even if aoe is violating one of the last true standing class limitations. I don't see that ever going live.
<br />
The list above gives you a much more relyable source of damage from the pet on mobs that are melee resistant (emp ssra for instance), and also limits its ability to Do Something Really Stupid Master(tm)
<br />
Limiting the pet to single target prevents a whole host of issues, namely that NPCs do not follow the # of target limitations players do, so a fire pet could be used to basicly PBAOE at that point.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
